methods.label: getIdentityParam
methods.comment: Gets a parameter from the JWT token for an identity service associated with this integration service, or an empty string if no identity service is assigned to this integration service.
methods.codesample:
&apos;The following sample gets the base64-encoded JWT token passed from the identity service, which might be used to connect to a remote database
Dim jwt as String
jwt = VoltMxRequest.getIdentityParam()

methods.label: getInputParam
methods.comment: Gets an input parameter passed to Foundry.
methods.codesample:
&apos;The following sample gets username parameter and validates it&apos;s not blank
Dim username as String
username = VoltMxRequest.getInputParam(&quot;username&quot;)
If (username = &quot;&quot;) Then
    VoltMxResult.setErrorMessage(&quot;Username is required&quot;)
    Return False
End If

methods.label: addInputParam
methods.comment: Adds an input parameter for the Foundry integration service. This proxies the corresponding function in VotMxResult object. Only relevant for preprocessors.
methods.codesample:
&apos;The following code would add a username from a session parameter to the subsequent request, if available. This could be used to lazy-load the value.
Dim username as String
username = VoltMxSession.getAttribute(&quot;username&quot;)
If (username != &quot;&quot;) Then
    Call VoltMxRequest.addInputParam(&quot;username&quot;, username)
Else
   &apos; E.g. extract from base64-decoded JWT token)
End If
